org.deeplearning4j.arbiter.optimize.api.data

Interface DataSource

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable

    public interface DataSource
extends Serializable
    DataSource: defines where the data should come from for training and testing. Note that implementations must have a no-argument contsructor
    Author:
    Alex Black

    • Method Detail

      • configure

        void configure(Properties properties)
        Configure the current data source with the specified properties Note: These properties are fixed for the training instance, and are optionally provided by the user at the configuration stage. The properties could be anything - and are usually specific to each DataSource implementation. For example, values such as batch size could be set using these properties
        Parameters:
        properties - Properties to apply to the data source instance

      • trainData

        Object trainData()
        Get test data to be used for the optimization. Usually a DataSetIterator or MultiDataSetIterator

        Object testData()
        Get test data to be used for the optimization. Usually a DataSetIterator or MultiDataSetIterator

        Class<?> getDataType()

        Returns:
        Class of the objects returned by trainData and testData
